1
00:01:25,480 --> 00:01:26,280
How did it go today?

2
00:01:27,799 --> 00:01:30,040
I sold a poem here for ten taels of silver.

3
00:01:30,120 --> 00:01:31,840
Let's go drink at Yihongyuan tonight.

4
00:01:32,079 --> 00:01:34,159
Brother, your literary talent is truly extraordinary!

5
00:01:34,599 --> 00:01:35,959
Let's go. We won't stop until we're drunk!

6
00:01:36,359 --> 00:01:36,840
Let's go.

7
00:01:37,079 --> 00:01:37,640
Thank you.

8
00:01:44,599 --> 00:01:45,319
What a waste of a trip.

9
00:01:46,120 --> 00:01:47,480
Not a single decent poem.

10
00:01:47,879 --> 00:01:50,319
Just a bunch of freeloaders.

11
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:53,920
I wasted the name Top Scholar Pavilion on this place.

12
00:01:54,879 --> 00:01:55,319
Your Maj...

13
00:01:57,159 --> 00:01:57,920
Master.

14
00:01:58,680 --> 00:02:01,359
Great poetry is rare to come by.

15
00:02:02,040 --> 00:02:03,159
Let's come back another day.

16
00:02:03,359 --> 00:02:04,359
I'm not coming back. Let's go.

17
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:10,000
Who are you?

18
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:11,800
Why are you blocking our way?

19
00:02:11,960 --> 00:02:12,800
Don't be nervous.

20
00:02:13,039 --> 00:02:14,159
I'm not a bad guy.

21
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:17,000
Are you two looking to buy poetry?

22
00:02:19,240 --> 00:02:20,319
Looking at you,

23
00:02:20,520 --> 00:02:22,199
you seem like a down-and-out scholar.

24
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:22,919
What,

25
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:24,479
got poems to sell?

26
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:28,639
I'm skilled in all forms of poetry.

27
00:02:29,080 --> 00:02:30,759
Just tell me what you'd like.

28
00:02:30,879 --> 00:02:31,599
If you're not satisfied,

29
00:02:32,039 --> 00:02:33,159
no charge.

30
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,159
Young as you are,

31
00:02:35,479 --> 00:02:37,000
you sure talk big.

32
00:02:38,639 --> 00:02:39,439
Like I said,

33
00:02:39,599 --> 00:02:41,400
no charge if you're not happy.

34
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:43,960
Why not buy one first to try?

35
00:02:44,599 --> 00:02:45,599
Buy more only if you like it.

36
00:02:46,280 --> 00:02:47,280
When it comes to business,

37
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,599
I'm all about being fair and square.

38
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:51,639
Fair to everyone, young and old.

39
00:02:52,719 --> 00:02:53,439
Try it?

40
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:56,240
Poetry isn't exactly food.

41
00:02:56,439 --> 00:02:57,680
How can you taste that stuff?

42
00:02:58,159 --> 00:03:00,400
You don't exactly look like a refined scholar.

43
00:03:00,599 --> 00:03:02,400
One look and I can tell, you're a swindler.

44
00:03:02,520 --> 00:03:03,240
Let's go, Master.

45
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:04,080
Let's head home.

46
00:03:06,159 --> 00:03:07,840
Who says I'm a swindler?

47
00:03:09,840 --> 00:03:10,879
I'm telling you,

48
00:03:11,879 --> 00:03:14,240
I'll soon shake the literary world.

49
00:03:14,400 --> 00:03:16,639
My poems will be worth a fortune.

50
00:03:17,599 --> 00:03:18,840
If you don't buy now,

51
00:03:19,319 --> 00:03:20,680
you'll regret it later.

52
00:03:23,400 --> 00:03:25,080
Shake the literary world?

53
00:03:26,360 --> 00:03:27,280
You're killing m...

54
00:03:27,599 --> 00:03:28,520
You crack me up.

55
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:31,319
Looking all sissy like that,

56
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,000
do you even know poetry?

57
00:03:33,759 --> 00:03:34,439
Who are you talking about?

58
00:03:34,759 --> 00:03:36,120
Who are you calling sissy?

59
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,159
Who's a sissy?

60
00:03:37,319 --> 00:03:38,240
I'm plenty manly!

61
00:03:38,879 --> 00:03:39,560
Whoa.

62
00:03:40,319 --> 00:03:42,039
He's not really a eunuch, is he?

63
00:03:42,719 --> 00:03:44,000
Traveling around with a eunuch...

64
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:45,319
Then his master

65
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,039
must be royalty?

66
00:03:47,039 --> 00:03:47,680
Give it back.

67
00:03:49,319 --> 00:03:50,560
If you don't believe me,

68
00:03:51,479 --> 00:03:52,280
go ahead and test me.

69
00:03:53,759 --> 00:03:54,439
Alright, alright.

70
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:55,400
Interesting.

71
00:03:55,639 --> 00:03:57,360
I've got nothing to do today anyway.

72
00:03:57,439 --> 00:03:59,560
Let's give your poems a taste.

73
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:02,000
Please.

74
00:04:03,439 --> 00:04:05,919
How about a white goose

75
00:04:06,479 --> 00:04:07,199
as the topic?

76
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,800
Goose, goose, goose,

77
00:04:11,879 --> 00:04:14,560
bending its neck, singing to the sky.

78
00:04:15,439 --> 00:04:18,519
White feathers float on green water,

79
00:04:19,639 --> 00:04:23,319
red feet stir the clear waves.

80
00:04:25,959 --> 00:04:27,000
Rooster, rooster, rooster,

81
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:31,040
crowing at the sun.

82
00:04:31,639 --> 00:04:33,839
Red crest atop his head,

83
00:04:34,560 --> 00:04:38,399
yellow feet thin and long.

84
00:04:41,040 --> 00:04:43,199
"Emperor thin and long"?

85
00:04:43,519 --> 00:04:44,720
You're quite good at drawing parallels.

86
00:04:44,839 --> 00:04:45,920
You, you...

87
00:04:46,040 --> 00:04:47,279
That poem you just recited,

88
00:04:47,879 --> 00:04:49,360
though lacking deep meaning,

89
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,199
wins by being catchy.

90
00:04:51,319 --> 00:04:53,040
And it suits the scene perfectly.

91
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,360
Great for teaching children.

92
00:04:56,839 --> 00:04:58,600
This Master truly knows quality.

93
00:04:59,319 --> 00:05:02,120
Unlike some others.

94
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:03,720
Alright.

95
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:06,399
I'll buy this poem.

96
00:05:06,639 --> 00:05:07,240
How much?

97
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:09,680
Finally, my first sale!

98
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,879
One tael isn't too much, right?

99
00:05:13,279 --> 00:05:15,680
A hundred taels? Why not just rob me?

100
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:16,399
It's worth it.

101
00:05:16,839 --> 00:05:18,199
A hundred taels it is.

102
00:05:24,120 --> 00:05:25,680
This uncle truly has

103
00:05:26,319 --> 00:05:29,319
a keen eye for gems

104
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:34,160
and taste finer than a jade lute

105
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:36,399
That line's quite good too

106
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:37,439
Add fifty more

107
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,879
With 150 taels in hand,

108
00:05:41,199 --> 00:05:42,959
I can solve Xiao Mei's pressing matter.

109
00:05:44,199 --> 00:05:46,639
This lad does have some real talent.

110
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:47,720
Let me test him further.

111
00:05:47,839 --> 00:05:48,600
Come, young friend,

112
00:05:48,759 --> 00:05:49,720
let's sit down and chat.

113
00:05:50,040 --> 00:05:50,439
Alright.

114
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:04,879
Uncle,

115
00:06:05,639 --> 00:06:07,079
winter's almost here,

116
00:06:07,720 --> 00:06:08,279
and look at me,

117
00:06:08,759 --> 00:06:10,399
still wearing thin clothes.

118
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:12,319
To be honest with you,

119
00:06:13,000 --> 00:06:13,879
my whole family

120
00:06:14,759 --> 00:06:16,319
is all dead and gone.

121
00:06:17,759 --> 00:06:19,240
Only me and my little maid are left,

122
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:21,639
the two of us depending on each other.

123
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:23,199
We

124
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,279
haven't had a proper meal

125
00:06:26,160 --> 00:06:27,959
in several days now.

126
00:06:29,399 --> 00:06:30,920
Eat whatever you want, don't hold back.

127
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:32,079
Don't mind if I do, Uncle.

128
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:33,199
Yes, yes, don't be shy.

129
00:06:34,600 --> 00:06:35,120
Eat, eat.

130
00:06:35,879 --> 00:06:36,360
Eat.

131
00:06:37,240 --> 00:06:37,839
Eat, eat.

132
00:06:38,160 --> 00:06:39,120
Eat, eat, eat.

133
00:06:41,920 --> 00:06:42,439
Eat.

134
00:06:43,120 --> 00:06:44,360
Slow, slow down.

135
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:52,600
Slow down.

136
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:54,560
Don't choke.

137
00:06:57,079 --> 00:06:57,920
Yes, sir.

138
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:06,560
Young friend,

139
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,639
seeing you compose poems on the spot,

140
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:10,079
your talent must be extraordinary.

141
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:11,759
May I ask your name

142
00:07:11,959 --> 00:07:13,199
and where you live?

143
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:14,959
My name is

144
00:07:16,360 --> 00:07:17,199
Lan Xing.

145
00:07:18,120 --> 00:07:20,360
Looks like I can't return to Lan Xing.

146
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:24,000
Let this be a tribute to my old home.

147
00:07:24,240 --> 00:07:25,199
Lan Xing.

148
00:07:25,759 --> 00:07:27,639
Is there a Lan family in the capital?

149
00:07:28,120 --> 00:07:30,920
This lad probably isn't telling the truth.

150
00:07:31,639 --> 00:07:34,040
And what is your name, Uncle?

151
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,399
Where do you reside?

152
00:07:35,759 --> 00:07:36,360
I am

153
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:37,800
Tian Xuan.

154
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,600
"Heaven is dark, Earth is yellow"—

155
00:07:40,160 --> 00:07:41,240
You claim two of those characters.

156
00:07:42,279 --> 00:07:43,000
What a fine name.

157
00:07:43,480 --> 00:07:44,480
Anyone with such a name

158
00:07:45,199 --> 00:07:46,519
must be a person of high status.

159
00:07:47,240 --> 00:07:48,199
If I can connect with him,

160
00:07:48,879 --> 00:07:49,480
from now on

161
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,560
I'll never worry about earning silver again.

162
00:07:52,439 --> 00:07:55,399
Didn't you say you're a master of all poetry?

163
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,959
Come on, give me a few more.

164
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:59,079
Don't be in such a hurry.

165
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:01,240
You haven't paid for the last one yet.

166
00:08:02,160 --> 00:08:04,120
We'll talk about the rest after.

167
00:08:06,920 --> 00:08:07,759
Here, here.

168
00:08:18,360 --> 00:08:20,240
Uncle, you're truly my savior.

169
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:22,000
My admiration for you, Uncle,

170
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:24,399
is like a mighty river,

171
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:28,040
flowing without end.

172
00:08:28,720 --> 00:08:29,519
Alright, alright.

173
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,679
So what other poems do you have to sell me?

174
00:08:34,039 --> 00:08:35,600
Oh, I've got plenty.

175
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,440
Whatever kind of poem you want, Uncle,

176
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:39,000
I've got it.

177
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,039
Li Bai, Du Fu, Wang Anshi.

178
00:08:42,360 --> 00:08:45,279
A hundred taels a poem, a real bargain.

179
00:08:46,080 --> 00:08:48,480
Cows are flying in the sky,

180
00:08:48,679 --> 00:08:51,720
and you're down here blowing the hot air.

181
00:08:52,720 --> 00:08:53,879
When it comes to bragging on the ground,

182
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:56,360
I must admit defeat.

183
00:08:58,320 --> 00:08:59,600
Bring it on.

184
00:09:00,440 --> 00:09:02,679
True gold fears no fire.

185
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:06,600
Recently, our nation suffered losses at the frontier.

186
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:08,720
The enemy state even sent

187
00:09:09,000 --> 00:09:11,600
the nanmu wood used to build their capital's pavilions

188
00:09:11,720 --> 00:09:13,120
all the way to our capital.

189
00:09:13,320 --> 00:09:13,879
As a subtle taunt:

190
00:09:14,039 --> 00:09:16,559
one day, they'll trample over Da Xuan.

191
00:09:17,039 --> 00:09:19,000
Many of our generals are filled with resentment.

192
00:09:19,639 --> 00:09:20,159
Lan Xing,

193
00:09:20,320 --> 00:09:21,960
let's take the frontier as the theme.

194
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,720
How about composing a poem?

195
00:09:27,360 --> 00:09:28,919
Stumped now, aren't you?

196
00:09:29,399 --> 00:09:30,639
Slap in the face, huh?

197
00:09:32,399 --> 00:09:34,279
Which eye saw me getting slapped?

198
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:36,279
Just spit out a poem then.

199
00:09:38,200 --> 00:09:40,200
You look like you're not even of age yet,

200
00:09:40,360 --> 00:09:41,879
unaware of the battlefield's perils.

201
00:09:42,200 --> 00:09:44,200
This topic is genuinely a bit difficult.

202
00:09:44,879 --> 00:09:46,200
No harm in giving it some thought.

203
00:09:46,679 --> 00:09:47,159
Got it.

204
00:09:50,639 --> 00:09:52,000
A barbarian flask hangs at his arm,

205
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:54,440
his steed a fine purple stallion.

206
00:09:54,960 --> 00:09:57,039
West of Suiye City,

207
00:09:58,320 --> 00:10:00,360
the autumn moon hangs round.

208
00:10:01,279 --> 00:10:02,639
By imperial decree, swift as stars,

209
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:05,039
the precious sword is bestowed.

210
00:10:05,919 --> 00:10:07,399
Leaving His Majesty for one night,

211
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:11,360
to conquer Loulan.

